{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"wanted-mean-sloth","description":"## Why\n\nThe `optionality` workflow (lean-runtime / clean-core-wheel / per-extra / union checks)\ncasts NO Gerrit `Verified` vote — only `gerrit-verify.yaml` does, and it installs\n`.[dev]` (heavy stack present), so the no-extras clean-wheel RUNTIME check never runs\npre-merge. A module-scope heavy-import regression (pydantic_ai/httpx) recently reached\nmain this way. The static AST guard already runs in Verified via `make test`; the\nruntime/packaging jobs do not. Cost to add: ~0 critical-path latency (32s parallel vs\n~1235s macOS long pole), ~145 cheap Linux machine-seconds/run.\n\n## What\n\nExtract optionality's jobs into a `workflow_call` reusable workflow and invoke it from\nboth the push/PR lane and the Verified lane, so a clean-wheel/packaging failure blocks\nthe Verified vote. Incorporate the critical-review findings (mandatory items below).\n\n## Scope\n\n- New `.github/workflows/_optionality.yml` (`on: workflow_call`, inputs for the checkout\n  mode), `.github/actions/smart-checkout` composite, thin `optionality.yml` caller,\n  `gerrit-verify.yaml` gains an `optionality` job + it is added to `vote`'s `needs`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `optionality`'s jobs live in a reusable `workflow_call` workflow, invoked by both\n      `optionality.yml` (push/PR, branch-head checkout) and `gerrit-verify.yaml`.\n- [ ] The gerrit lane checks out the EXACT patchset via `checkout-gerrit-change-action`\n      (never plain `actions/checkout`, which would resolve to `main` and false-PASS).\n- [ ] The `optionality` job is added to `vote`'s `needs` so the run-level conclusion\n      aggregation sees a terminal optionality result before Verified is cast.\n- [ ] NO `secrets: inherit` on the reusable workflow; Gerrit values passed as plain\n      inputs only (prevents fork-PR exposure of GERRIT_SSH_PRIVKEY via the PR trigger).\n- [ ] The third-party `checkout-gerrit-change-action` is SHA-pinned to the same v1.0.2\n      commit gerrit-verify uses.\n- [ ] `_optionality.yml` declares `permissions: contents: read`; the optionality caller\n      job is pure `uses:` (no `steps:`) and independent of clear-vote/require-ticket.\n- [ ] Workflows parse/lint clean (actionlint if available) and the push-triggered\n      optionality run passes on the change; gerrit-verify runs the optionality job and\n      the Verified vote reflects it.","id":"15e7-f013-0cfb-494b","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Add optionality checks to the Gerrit Verified path via a workflow_call reusable workflow"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783791911061315001,"uuid":"d0b95067-2e0c-4cff-ac2b-c8599f4ed5c2"}